The Ondo State Deputy Governor and governorship candidate of the Zenith Labour Party, Hon Agboola Ajayi, has said he is the most
qualified among those vying for the governorship seat of the state in
the forthcoming governorship poll. Speaking at Ore, Odigbo local government area, at the campaign flag off a
rally of the ZLP, Ajayi accused the son of Governor Akeredolu of
collecting N403m state-owned from the recovered N43bn found stashed in
Zenith Bank since 2008. While assuring the voters in the state to vote for him, the Deputy
Governor promised to reduce tuition fees paid in the state-owned
tertiary institutions to N50,000. He said the tuition fees which were N25,000 before Akeredolu came to
power was increased to between N150,000 and N200,000 because Akeredolu
never cares for the people’s welfare. He said he would stop the use of consultants in doing government
business which he stated had made the Ondo civil service redundant. 